===Cityscape===
The city of Memphis is located in southwestern [[Tennessee]] and sits on the eastern bank of the [[Mississippi River]]. It is the regional hub for a [[tri-state area]] of [[Arkansas]], [[Mississippi]] and Tennessee. [[Interstate 40]] enters the city from the [[Ordinal direction|northeast]], and loops above the central part of the city, exiting across the Mississippi River and travelling to the [[west]]. [[Interstate 55]] approaches the city from the [[south]] and connects with [[Interstate 240 (Tennessee)|I-240]], which completes the loop around central Memphis with I-40, and also leaves to the west. [[U.S. Highway 72]] leaves the city traveling to the [[Ordinal directions|southeast]].  The west end of [http://www.geocities.com/usend7079/End078/end078.htm U.S. Highway 78] begins in Memphis, TN on Linden Avenue at the intersection of 2nd Street.  As it leaves Memphis, US 78 follows Lamar Avenue, historically known as ''Pidgeon Roost Road'' for the nestings of [[passenger pigeon]]s formerly in the vicinity.  The east end of U.S. Highway 78 terminates in Charleston, South Carolina.

===Aquifer===
Shelby Country is located over four natural aquifers, one of which is recognized as the "Memphis sand aquifer" or simply as the "Memphis aquifer." This particular water source, located some 350 to 1100 feet underground, is stated to contain "more than 100 trillion gallons of water" by Memphis Light, Gas, and Water,[http://mlgw.com/SubView.php?key=about_ourutilservices] which draws, verifies the cleanliness of, and distributes the water to over 250,000 customers. Furthermore, in the time since the tapping of the well in 1887, the aquifer has only descended 125 feet, suggesting a reliable water source in Memphis for years to come.[http://www.mhhe.com/biosci/pae/environmentalscience/casestudies/case9.mhtml] Most Memphians recognize this as their primary water source, and take great regional pride in their possession of the aquifer.

==Sections/ Suburbs==
''See also: [[Memphis Metropolitan Area]]''

Memphis is marked by five major districts, with smaller districts lying within their borders. These are [[Downtown Memphis, Tennessee|Downtown]], [[Midtown, Memphis|Midtown]], [[Raleigh, Memphis|North Memphis]], [[South Memphis, Memphis|South Memphis]], and [[East Memphis, Memphis|East Memphis]].

